 :sorcerer's apprentice mode: /n./ [from Goethe's "Der Zauberlehrling" via
Paul Dukas's "L'apprenti sorcier" the film "Fantasia"] A bug in a protocol
where, under some circumstances, the receipt of a message causes multiple
messages to be sent, each of which, when received, triggers the same bug.
Used esp. of such behavior caused by {bounce message} loops in {email}
software. Compare {broadcast storm}, {network meltdown}, {software laser},
{ARMM}.